<header>
<h1>Chatbot Evaluation</h1>
<p>Evaluation of a Chatbot Deployed in Production</p>
</header>

<section>
<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>
Chatbots are software programs that interact with users using text or voice.
Many organizations deploy chatbots in production environments to provide
customer support, answer queries, and automate tasks. Evaluating a chatbot
helps understand its effectiveness, reliability, and user satisfaction.
</p>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Advantages of Chatbots</h2>
<ul>
<li>24/7 customer support without human intervention.</li>
<li>Quick responses to user queries.</li>
<li>Reduces workload for human agents.</li>
<li>Handles multiple users at the same time.</li>
<li>Improves user engagement and experience.</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Challenges of Chatbots</h2>
<ul>
<li>Difficulty understanding complex user queries.</li>
<li>Limited responses if training data is insufficient.</li>
<li>May give incorrect or irrelevant answers.</li>
<li>Requires regular updates and maintenance.</li>
<li>Security and privacy concerns.</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Evaluation Parameters</h2>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Accuracy</td>
<td>Correctness of chatbot responses</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Response Time</td>
<td>Speed of answering user queries</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>User Satisfaction</td>
<td>How satisfied users are with responses</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Scalability</td>
<td>Ability to handle many users</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Reliability</td>
<td>Consistency of chatbot performance</td>
</tr>

</table>

</section>

<section>
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>
Chatbots are useful tools for automating communication and improving service
efficiency. However, proper evaluation is necessary to ensure accuracy,
security, and user satisfaction. Continuous improvement and monitoring help
make chatbots more reliable in real-world applications.
</p>
</section>

